1
00:00:17,330 --> 00:00:22,840
So, why do you keep provoking them? They think you're the bad guy.

2
00:00:23,530 --> 00:00:26,620
I don't care what they think.

3
00:00:29,200 --> 00:00:32,640
The more I think about it, the more baffled I get.

4
00:00:32,640 --> 00:00:36,190
There are plenty of seniors. How dare they order you to protest?

5
00:00:36,190 --> 00:00:40,570
They're obviously trying to dump it all on you because they don't want to be dragged to Namsan.

6
00:00:41,360 --> 00:00:45,690
It's my choice. I'm not doing it because they're making me.

7
00:00:47,560 --> 00:00:50,850
Sure. Whatever, Mr. Fighter.

8
00:00:51,860 --> 00:00:55,790
Everything you do bothers me.

9
00:00:55,790 --> 00:00:58,990
And why's your taste in music so bad?

10
00:00:59,650 --> 00:01:02,940
You told me to request a song I want to listen to.

11
00:01:02,940 --> 00:01:05,420
Why must you nitpick about everything?

12
00:01:05,420 --> 00:01:07,480
We really don't see eye to eye.

13
00:01:08,010 --> 00:01:12,810
You say that all the time. Why did you team up with me, then?

14
00:01:12,810 --> 00:01:15,170
Why do you think so?

15
00:01:15,840 --> 00:01:18,860
Because there's no one to write the lyrics.

16
00:01:18,860 --> 00:01:22,680
I'm sorry, but there are plenty of people who can write the lyrics.

17
00:01:22,680 --> 00:01:25,720
Then what? Because I'm nice?

18
00:01:25,720 --> 00:01:29,950
Wow, saying you're nice with your own words. Are you nuts?

19
00:01:31,950 --> 00:01:35,810
Everyone says I'm nice except for you.

20
00:01:35,810 --> 00:01:37,810
They say they like me because I'm like a saint.

21
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:41,150
Wow.

22
00:01:44,950 --> 00:01:49,640
Kim Kyeong Soo, don't be fooled.

23
00:01:49,640 --> 00:01:52,260
You're no saint.

24
00:02:09,180 --> 00:02:12,640
You punks, do you think you're on a picnic now?

25
00:02:12,640 --> 00:02:14,440
Hurry up! You're all so slow.

26
00:02:14,440 --> 00:02:16,660
You slackers.

27
00:02:36,260 --> 00:02:38,390
Hee Tae, the ambulance is coming in.

28
00:02:38,390 --> 00:02:40,060
Oh, all right.

29
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:48,970
[Episode 10: Virtue, Hypocrisy, Utmost Effort]

30
00:02:50,510 --> 00:02:55,590
The Martial Law Army Headquarters... can't you write it properly? What is this?

31
00:02:55,590 --> 00:02:57,350
Did you count it properly?

32
00:02:57,350 --> 00:02:59,350
It should be right.

33
00:03:11,140 --> 00:03:12,920
What are you doing here?

34
00:03:12,920 --> 00:03:15,540
Didn't you go up to Seoul to get married?

35
00:03:19,140 --> 00:03:22,670
I'll be on my way after I grab some medical supplies. So mind your own business.

36
00:03:22,670 --> 00:03:27,210
Why? Did your father-in-law ask you to keep an eye out on what's happening here?

37
00:03:27,210 --> 00:03:28,370
What?

38
00:03:28,370 --> 00:03:29,610
Am I wrong?

39
00:03:29,610 --> 00:03:34,700
Are you the Grim Reaper? Everyone who sees you disappears.

40
00:03:34,700 --> 00:03:38,640
Did Hye Gun also go missing after meeting up with you?

41
00:03:40,170 --> 00:03:42,390
It wasn't her. It was me.

42
00:03:44,530 --> 00:03:47,680
The person he met before he disappeared was me.

43
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:50,610
Then, does that make me the Grim Reaper, too?

44
00:03:50,610 --> 00:03:54,080
Why are you taking your anger on preventive custody out on her?

45
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:55,420
That's because her fiance—

46
00:03:55,420 --> 00:03:58,160
She ran away from home.

47
00:03:58,160 --> 00:03:59,250
What?

48
00:03:59,250 --> 00:04:02,720
She ran away from home. Can't you tell by looking at her?

49
00:04:02,720 --> 00:04:07,070
Both of us haven't even been able to take a shower for the last few days, taking care of the injured.

50
00:04:07,070 --> 00:04:11,870
So stop wasting your energy on someone who's on the same side as you.

51
00:04:24,420 --> 00:04:25,800
Bu Yeong!

52
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:28,130
That... That...

53
00:04:28,130 --> 00:04:29,990
Are you done writing?

54
00:04:29,990 --> 00:04:34,420
What's wrong with your writing? Write it bigger.

55
00:04:35,860 --> 00:04:37,750
Can you lower your head?

56
00:04:37,750 --> 00:04:43,030
Hwang Hee Tae, who has only been here two days, is better at that than Dr. Song,

57
00:04:43,030 --> 00:04:46,190
who has been an intern here for half a year. Looks like he's already adjusted well.

58
00:04:46,190 --> 00:04:47,640
I know, right?

59
00:04:47,640 --> 00:04:53,130
- He passed the exam with the highest score, you know.
- Don't blatantly stare at him.

60
00:05:07,260 --> 00:05:11,620
Is there anyone that's free? Can anyone take care of Kim Deok Bae?

61
00:05:11,620 --> 00:05:14,800
Kim Deok Bae? The delirious patient? The one who beats up everyone?

62
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:17,870
Yes, his symptoms aren't getting any better.

63
00:05:17,870 --> 00:05:20,220
Give him more sedatives and take this urinary bag—

64
00:05:20,220 --> 00:05:21,880
What?

65
00:05:21,880 --> 00:05:24,630
- Attach this urinary bag, too.
- Goodness.

66
00:05:32,910 --> 00:05:34,780
I'll do it.

67
00:05:35,460 --> 00:05:37,380
Will you?

68
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:46,020
Myeong Hee, what are you doing?

69
00:05:46,020 --> 00:05:47,160
Huh?

70
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:51,760
We need to admit a new patient together. An emergency patient.

71
00:05:52,300 --> 00:05:53,760
We'll be right back.

72
00:05:54,990 --> 00:05:56,560
Wait—

73
00:05:58,140 --> 00:06:01,850
He's adjusted too well.

74
00:06:02,420 --> 00:06:03,830
Is anyone coming?

75
00:06:03,830 --> 00:06:06,120
I'm going!

76
00:06:06,120 --> 00:06:09,710
How many times do I need to tell you? If no one asks, don't volunteer.

77
00:06:09,710 --> 00:06:11,390
Why do you keep doing all the grunt work?

78
00:06:11,390 --> 00:06:15,270
I don't pick and choose the work I do. I just do what I can.

79
00:06:16,440 --> 00:06:19,770
Then, are the other people not doing their work because they can't do it?

80
00:06:19,770 --> 00:06:24,050
See! They keep handing you the work because they know you'll do it.

81
00:06:24,050 --> 00:06:26,920
You do all the grunt work, too!

82
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:28,420
The mattress window work from yesterday—

83
00:06:28,420 --> 00:06:30,220
Do you think I did it because I wanted to?

84
00:06:30,220 --> 00:06:32,620
With all the bullets coming through the window?

85
00:06:32,620 --> 00:06:35,370
I did it because you said you would!

86
00:06:35,370 --> 00:06:36,800
If I didn't do it, you would have!

87
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:38,510
All right, enough with the nagging!

88
00:06:38,510 --> 00:06:41,480
Nagging? It's all because I'm thinking about you!

89
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:43,950
A patient is coming.

90
00:06:45,270 --> 00:06:49,440
[Emergency Medical Center]

91
00:06:53,230 --> 00:06:56,770
The patient is 18 and he's been shot in the hand and lower abdomen.

92
00:06:56,770 --> 00:06:58,570
A bullet wound?

93
00:07:05,420 --> 00:07:08,960
Let's go straight to the OR. Make sure to prepare enough blood.

94
00:07:17,530 --> 00:07:21,890
These bastards. Using guns meant to protect the country on civilians?

95
00:07:21,890 --> 00:07:24,550
Does this make any sense?

96
00:07:25,110 --> 00:07:27,820
What wrong did the child do?

97
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:33,380
Jeong Tae,

98
00:07:33,380 --> 00:07:37,450
sleep at home. I'll give you a ride back and forth.

99
00:07:37,450 --> 00:07:42,400
I'm really okay. Nobody went home. Everyone is staying here.

100
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:48,100
I'm worried, and I don't know when your dad will ask for you.

101
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:50,540
He never asks for me.

102
00:07:52,290 --> 00:07:53,640
What?

103
00:07:55,470 --> 00:07:58,910
Anyway, I don't want to. I want to stay here.

104
00:08:03,830 --> 00:08:06,440
Yes, Jeong Tae's mother.

105
00:08:06,440 --> 00:08:10,160
We're only training within the dorm area.

106
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:14,520
We're not going out at all, so don't worry about Jeong Tae.

107
00:08:14,520 --> 00:08:17,610
Please contact me if anything happens, Coach.

108
00:08:17,610 --> 00:08:19,430
Yes, yes, of course.

109
00:08:19,430 --> 00:08:21,760
Take care.

110
00:08:25,780 --> 00:08:27,820
Yes!

111
00:08:27,820 --> 00:08:31,270
We're only training within the dorm area!

112
00:08:33,990 --> 00:08:36,770
What did he say? Is everything all right with Myeong Soo?

113
00:08:37,320 --> 00:08:40,960
He said they're only training within the dorm area, and that there's nothing to worry about.

114
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:49,580
If it bothers you, should we bring him here? I can go pick him up.

115
00:08:49,580 --> 00:08:53,150
It's probably better for him to stay in the dorms rather than seeing things he doesn't have to.

116
00:08:53,150 --> 00:08:55,270
And it's probably safer.

117
00:09:16,170 --> 00:09:18,100
So quick!

118
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:25,730
Are you crazy?

119
00:09:25,730 --> 00:09:29,080
Soo Geon, get out of here now!

120
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:31,740
Sergeant Hong!

121
00:09:31,740 --> 00:09:34,910
Don't come close! Don't come close or I'll kill him!

122
00:09:34,910 --> 00:09:38,560
This crazy bastard! Kim Kyeong Soo, what are you doing? Hurry, shoot!

123
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:40,640
Hurry, shoot!

124
00:09:42,790 --> 00:09:44,750
Stay still!

125
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:46,880
Hurry, shoot!

126
00:10:01,270 --> 00:10:06,200
Due to the military's excessive use of force, hundred of innocent civilians have been injured.

127
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:08,410
Someone even died yesterday.

128
00:10:08,410 --> 00:10:11,220
You need to order the airborne troops to withdraw immediately.

129
00:10:11,220 --> 00:10:15,740
- Is there any guarantee that simply ordering a withdrawal will solve the problem?
- What are you saying?

130
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:17,980
Do you think they were dispatched for no reason?

131
00:10:17,980 --> 00:10:21,560
It's more important to suppress the mob that's causing this whole frenzy.

132
00:10:21,560 --> 00:10:24,770
Whose side are you on right now?

133
00:10:24,770 --> 00:10:29,880
We're gathered here to sort this situation out. We're not here to take sides.

134
00:10:31,440 --> 00:10:34,720
Or perhaps, Father,

135
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:38,700
are you here to represent one side in particular?

136
00:10:38,700 --> 00:10:40,960
Please watch your mouth.

137
00:10:40,960 --> 00:10:43,030
- You're the ones who should watch your mouths.
- What?

138
00:10:43,030 --> 00:10:45,160
- What did you say?
- Did I say something wrong?

139
00:10:45,160 --> 00:10:47,440
How could you say that to an assemblyman?

140
00:10:47,970 --> 00:10:51,820
These are the minutes from today's emergency committee meeting.

141
00:10:54,350 --> 00:10:59,280
Did you participate in the meeting and write this yourself?

142
00:10:59,280 --> 00:11:03,190
No, Sir. The officials who were present at the meeting wrote them—

143
00:11:03,190 --> 00:11:09,300
Mr. Hwang, we are in positions that require some legwork.

144
00:11:09,300 --> 00:11:14,780
How will you control the situation if you sit behind a desk and simply receive reports?

145
00:11:14,780 --> 00:11:19,050
This really troubles me.

146
00:11:19,050 --> 00:11:23,690
I mean it's safe to say that martial law has been expanded mainly because of Gwangju.

147
00:11:24,780 --> 00:11:28,310
I'll make sure to participate in future meetings myself.

148
00:11:46,810 --> 00:11:51,080
- You loaded the bullets backward. Did you do this on purpose?
- I'm sorry, sir.

149
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:54,830
Hey, did you join this place to protect the commies?

150
00:11:54,830 --> 00:11:57,540
How can you call yourself a soldier?

151
00:11:57,540 --> 00:12:00,220
Answer me, you punk.

152
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:05,740
How dare you load your bullets backward? You stupid punk.

153
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:10,610
You're a darn disgrace.

154
00:12:26,830 --> 00:12:31,690
Corporal Lee, I'm sorry about what happened earlier.

155
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:34,070
I just couldn't get myself to shoot—

156
00:12:34,070 --> 00:12:36,680
Do you think I fired that shot because I wanted to?

157
00:12:38,700 --> 00:12:43,670
Hey, Kim Kyung Soo. Do you think that makes you a nice person?

158
00:12:46,100 --> 00:12:51,750
This is the army. If you don't shoot, I have to.

159
00:12:51,750 --> 00:12:55,620
Can you call yourself nice if you force things on others to keep your own hands clean?

160
00:12:56,300 --> 00:12:59,800
That's what you call being selfish.

161
00:12:59,800 --> 00:13:01,800
I'm sorry, Sir.

162
00:13:06,820 --> 00:13:09,890
If you don't want to shoot anyone, arrest them as quickly as you can,

163
00:13:11,120 --> 00:13:13,420
before someone else shoots.

164
00:13:30,310 --> 00:13:33,050
What on Earth is that sound? I've been hearing it all day.

165
00:13:33,050 --> 00:13:35,680
Don't worry. It's probably nothing.

166
00:13:35,680 --> 00:13:39,320
Brother, it's time to take your medicine.

167
00:13:42,340 --> 00:13:45,820
Did Soo Chan really go to work this morning?

168
00:13:45,820 --> 00:13:49,380
Why? Is he not answering the phone at the office?

169
00:13:49,380 --> 00:13:51,950
Did you actually see Soo Chan leave?

170
00:13:53,730 --> 00:13:56,300
Tell me. What is going on?

171
00:13:57,630 --> 00:14:01,480
Brother, you need to calm down first.

172
00:14:01,480 --> 00:14:05,050
Tell me! What happened to Soo Chan?

173
00:14:19,900 --> 00:14:23,520
Sir.

174
00:14:24,650 --> 00:14:27,510
Over here. A person has collapsed.

175
00:14:27,510 --> 00:14:31,340
A man has collapsed. Please...

176
00:14:32,920 --> 00:14:35,890
- My Gosh.
- Who told you to move?

177
00:14:35,890 --> 00:14:39,660
Do you want to die? Get back to your position.

178
00:14:42,420 --> 00:14:46,640
What are you all looking at? Eyes down!

179
00:14:48,860 --> 00:14:50,680
Take him away.

180
00:15:09,090 --> 00:15:11,890
Hey, get back to your position, you punk.

181
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:18,860
What? Who was arrested?

182
00:15:18,860 --> 00:15:22,160
Soo Ryun's older brother. I'm not sure,

183
00:15:22,160 --> 00:15:24,930
but can you check if he's really been arrested?

184
00:15:24,930 --> 00:15:27,250
What a hassle.

185
00:15:28,130 --> 00:15:30,110
Tell them I'll check.

186
00:15:31,170 --> 00:15:33,210
But what is going on?

187
00:15:33,210 --> 00:15:35,230
People are calling all day, asking me to find people.

188
00:15:35,230 --> 00:15:39,010
There's no need for you to know. Just keep to the house for now.

189
00:15:43,820 --> 00:15:45,510
By the way,

190
00:15:52,860 --> 00:15:55,050
has Hee Tae called?

191
00:15:57,370 --> 00:15:59,280
No.

192
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:06,440
You should check on him first. Don't sit back and do nothing just because he doesn't call first.

193
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:10,010
Father never asks about me.

194
00:16:13,900 --> 00:16:16,290
Why aren't you asking about Jung Tae?

195
00:16:17,910 --> 00:16:20,610
Why are you asking me that out of the blue?

196
00:16:20,610 --> 00:16:23,290
Jung Tae is your son, too.

197
00:16:23,290 --> 00:16:26,960
You haven't seen him in days. Aren't you worried about him?

198
00:16:26,960 --> 00:16:29,270
Do you think I have the time to worry about the kid?

199
00:16:29,270 --> 00:16:31,990
That's enough of your nonsense. Just give me that.

200
00:16:43,980 --> 00:16:46,800
I finally got in touch with Mr. Lee.

201
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:50,630
He'll be here early in the morning.

202
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:54,590
That's a relief.

203
00:16:56,890 --> 00:17:01,160
Once he gets here, let's leave immediately.

204
00:17:02,690 --> 00:17:04,560
Immediately?

205
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:10,000
Our plan was to stay here until Mr. Lee comes to get Jin Ah.

206
00:17:14,540 --> 00:17:17,160
What's with that face?

207
00:17:18,590 --> 00:17:20,760
It's not like that.

208
00:17:20,760 --> 00:17:25,930
Then, what is it? If something is bothering you, just tell me.

209
00:17:25,930 --> 00:17:28,440
It's just that...

210
00:17:28,440 --> 00:17:33,800
if we leave, the ones left will have to do more work.

211
00:17:34,430 --> 00:17:36,650
That's what I was worried about.

212
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:46,330
What? Were you thinking that I'm a pushover?

213
00:17:49,010 --> 00:17:53,910
No way. I was thinking you are such a good person.

214
00:17:55,910 --> 00:18:01,730
But listen, Myeong Hee. If you really want to be good, you must put yourself first.

215
00:18:01,730 --> 00:18:07,480
If you put others before yourself, that's hypocrisy, I think.

216
00:18:08,280 --> 00:18:11,390
Don't people normally call that a sacrifice?

217
00:18:12,310 --> 00:18:15,800
That's what other people would call it.

218
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:21,190
But to someone who loves you, it's hypocrisy.

219
00:18:24,350 --> 00:18:29,010
So, for now, let's put you and me first.

220
00:18:29,860 --> 00:18:31,540
Okay?

221
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:43,960
We'll be training indoors again today. Get ready and come out as quickly as you can.

222
00:18:47,500 --> 00:18:49,970
Gosh, I feel so cooped up.

223
00:18:49,970 --> 00:18:53,460
Why can't we go out?

224
00:18:53,460 --> 00:18:55,800
It's my birthday today and I'm stuck indoors all day.

225
00:18:55,800 --> 00:18:59,440
Oh, my. Is it your birthday today, Sung Il?

226
00:18:59,440 --> 00:19:02,330
Gosh, then we should celebrate.

227
00:19:02,330 --> 00:19:06,400
You said you love comic books, right? Should we go borrow some comics?

228
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:09,530
If we can't even train outside, how can we go to the rental store?

229
00:19:09,530 --> 00:19:14,680
My gosh, we have two fast runners here. You two can rush over there and borrow some.

230
00:19:14,680 --> 00:19:18,230
Gather around. I have a plan.

231
00:19:23,460 --> 00:19:25,820
I'm going grocery shopping.

232
00:19:25,820 --> 00:19:27,840
See you.

233
00:19:38,560 --> 00:19:44,270
Excuse me, Coach. Do you have any digestive medicine?

234
00:19:44,270 --> 00:19:46,500
I think I have an upset stomach.

235
00:19:46,500 --> 00:19:50,670
You have an upset stomach? You, Jin Kyu?

236
00:19:50,670 --> 00:19:53,760
- Then let me prick your fingers.
- What?

237
00:19:54,830 --> 00:19:57,710
I think some medicine will do.

238
00:19:57,710 --> 00:20:02,810
Medicine won't do any good. Pricking all the fingers is the best remedy.

239
00:20:38,620 --> 00:20:40,470
It's still not going through?

240
00:20:40,470 --> 00:20:42,760
Are all the phones in town not working?

241
00:20:42,760 --> 00:20:45,370
No, just Gwangju.

242
00:20:46,420 --> 00:20:49,940
I can't take this. I need to go.

243
00:20:49,940 --> 00:20:52,150
Where? To Gwangju?

244
00:20:52,150 --> 00:20:54,150
By yourself?

245
00:20:54,150 --> 00:20:57,350
My Gosh, but the rumors are so disturbing.

246
00:20:57,350 --> 00:21:00,150
That's why I need to go.

247
00:21:05,010 --> 00:21:07,780
I hope there's nothing wrong.

248
00:21:09,690 --> 00:21:12,410
Hyun Cheol! Where are you going?

249
00:21:12,410 --> 00:21:15,290
Mother, I need to go to Gwangju. I'll be back soon.

250
00:21:15,290 --> 00:21:20,440
Don't go. Stay with me.

251
00:21:21,250 --> 00:21:25,470
Mother, have a seat.

252
00:21:25,470 --> 00:21:32,130
I'll be back as soon as I check that my kids are well.

253
00:21:37,060 --> 00:21:39,300
My gosh.

254
00:21:39,300 --> 00:21:42,360
My mother is so pretty.

255
00:21:47,530 --> 00:21:49,690
I'll be back.

256
00:21:49,690 --> 00:21:51,080
Don't come out.

257
00:21:51,080 --> 00:21:54,360
Be careful!

258
00:22:05,190 --> 00:22:09,000
Hey! Let's buy a Choco Pie, too! Instead of a cake.

259
