00:23:39,540 --> 00:23:43,600
♫ Long live our nation! ♫

276
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:47,510
♫ Rose of Sharon, thousand miles ♫

277
00:23:47,510 --> 00:23:50,940
Take aim!

278
00:23:50,940 --> 00:23:56,560
- What's that?
- What's going on?

279
00:24:45,540 --> 00:24:47,510
What is this noise?

280
00:25:39,640 --> 00:25:42,280
Run! Run!

281
00:26:20,100 --> 00:26:25,140
Go! There are no tickets! No tickets!

282
00:26:25,140 --> 00:26:28,950
What are you all doing gathered here?

283
00:26:28,950 --> 00:26:32,180
What do you mean? How could there be no tickets at a bus terminal?

284
00:26:32,180 --> 00:26:37,450
My goodness. All the buses going into Gwangju have been suspended.

285
00:26:37,450 --> 00:26:39,990
Then, what do I do if I want to go to Gwangju?

286
00:26:39,990 --> 00:26:43,710
The only way is to walk since all the cars are prohibited from entering, too.

287
00:26:43,710 --> 00:26:44,980
There are no buses?

288
00:26:44,980 --> 00:26:48,170
My goodness, there aren't any.

289
00:26:48,170 --> 00:26:51,320
What am I going to do?

290
00:26:51,320 --> 00:26:55,400
Excuse me. If you have a map, can I borrow it?

291
00:26:55,400 --> 00:26:57,590
To walk?

292
00:26:57,590 --> 00:27:01,610
Gwangju is shedding blood. Why would you go there?

293
00:27:02,790 --> 00:27:06,010
With legs like that, it'll take at least 10 days.

294
00:27:06,010 --> 00:27:10,980
Lee Jin Ah?

295
00:27:11,930 --> 00:27:15,200
J-Jin...

296
00:27:16,960 --> 00:27:18,930
Myeong Hee!

297
00:27:21,660 --> 00:27:23,790
Jin Ah...

298
00:27:26,710 --> 00:27:28,540
My goodness...

299
00:27:31,540 --> 00:27:33,640
Jin Ah!

300
00:27:35,790 --> 00:27:38,650
Jin Ah! Dad is here!

301
00:27:39,600 --> 00:27:41,490
Jin Ah!

302
00:27:42,890 --> 00:27:46,140
Wake up!

303
00:27:47,070 --> 00:27:49,460
She's regained consciousness.

304
00:27:49,460 --> 00:27:53,770
She's asleep right now because of the medication, so don't worry.

305
00:27:53,770 --> 00:27:56,700
Thankfully, the surgery results look good, too.

306
00:27:58,180 --> 00:28:01,180
I heard from Myeong Hee.

307
00:28:01,180 --> 00:28:04,020
Thank you, Doctor.

308
00:28:05,360 --> 00:28:07,490
I didn't do anything.

309
00:28:07,490 --> 00:28:12,250
If it weren't for Hee Tae, things could have gone very wrong.

310
00:28:13,630 --> 00:28:15,720
Life savior.

311
00:28:23,520 --> 00:28:26,300
Thank you, Doctor!

312
00:28:29,010 --> 00:28:34,120
My goodness! For saving my Jin Ah!

313
00:28:40,690 --> 00:28:42,590
Myeong Hee,

314
00:28:42,590 --> 00:28:45,260
go to the ER and say your goodbyes first.

315
00:28:45,260 --> 00:28:48,790
I'm going to see Seok Cheol while I'm here.

316
00:28:48,790 --> 00:28:52,140
Go ahead. Take your time.

317
00:28:55,390 --> 00:28:57,070
Myeong Hee!

318
00:28:58,510 --> 00:29:02,510
Earlier, I couldn't say anything because things were so hectic.

319
00:29:02,510 --> 00:29:05,530
On my way here, I passed the protest crowds

320
00:29:05,530 --> 00:29:10,350
and I saw the soldiers beating people up, shooting them. It's a total mess out there.

321
00:29:10,350 --> 00:29:13,340
You must have been surprised, not knowing what was going on.

322
00:29:13,340 --> 00:29:17,470
Me being surprised isn't what's important!

323
00:29:20,440 --> 00:29:24,560
Your brother... is he still in Gwangju?

324
00:29:24,560 --> 00:29:27,190
What about my brother?

325
00:29:27,190 --> 00:29:29,430
No matter how I think about it,

326
00:29:29,430 --> 00:29:34,080
I think I saw your brother earlier in that messy crowd.

327
00:29:40,270 --> 00:29:45,980
The way he looked, and even the trainers he was wearing. He looked just like your brother.

328
00:29:49,120 --> 00:29:54,580
I was busy dodging bullets in that hectic situation, so I couldn't take care of him.

329
00:30:02,810 --> 00:30:06,280
Two... zero... two...

330
00:30:15,290 --> 00:30:18,180
I'm going to spend all day answering these phone calls!

331
00:30:19,840 --> 00:30:23,840
Yes, we're only training within the dorm area.

332
00:30:25,230 --> 00:30:27,330
You want to talk to him?

333
00:30:27,330 --> 00:30:29,220
Hold on.

334
00:30:30,470 --> 00:30:33,880
Hwal Myeong Soo! Your sister is on the phone!

335
00:30:35,280 --> 00:30:37,260
Kim Myeong Soo!

336
00:30:39,460 --> 00:30:41,340
What is it?

337
00:30:41,340 --> 00:30:43,370
Where is Myeong Soo?

338
00:31:28,170 --> 00:31:30,850
What is it? Why are there so many patients with gun wounds?

339
00:31:30,850 --> 00:31:33,170
The military is firing ammo in groups!

340
00:31:33,170 --> 00:31:35,740
Firing ammo in groups?

341
00:31:35,740 --> 00:31:37,500
Are these all the patients?

342
00:31:37,500 --> 00:31:40,110
There's a truckload of patients that are left in the streets.

343
00:31:40,110 --> 00:31:42,430
We don't even have enough helping hands here!

344
00:31:42,430 --> 00:31:45,900
No one wants to go help either because they're even shooting at ambulances!

345
00:31:45,900 --> 00:31:49,090
What? Shooting at ambulances?

346
00:31:49,090 --> 00:31:52,820
They're even shooting at young children! They're not thinking about who or what they're shooting at.

347
00:31:53,860 --> 00:31:55,560
Let's go out!

348
00:31:55,560 --> 00:31:58,060
We can't leave patients out in the street like that!

349
00:31:58,060 --> 00:31:59,550
We'll take the cars

350
00:31:59,550 --> 00:32:01,780
and bring the patients ourselves.

351
00:32:01,780 --> 00:32:04,070
Is there anyone coming with me?

352
00:32:11,200 --> 00:32:14,020
What on Earth is happening!

353
00:32:15,200 --> 00:32:17,190
My son is going to be okay, right?

354
00:32:17,190 --> 00:32:20,450
Are you crazy? Where do you think you're going?

355
00:32:20,450 --> 00:32:22,350
To bring the patients.

356
00:32:22,350 --> 00:32:24,440
There are people on the streets wounded by gunshots.

357
00:32:24,440 --> 00:32:28,040
Are they the only ones on the streets? The military is everywhere, too.

358
00:32:28,040 --> 00:32:30,290
You want us to wait blindly?

359
00:32:30,290 --> 00:32:31,950
Someone has to go.

360
00:32:31,950 --> 00:32:34,940
So why does that someone have to be you?

361
00:32:34,940 --> 00:32:37,560
Do you have two lives?

362
00:32:40,880 --> 00:32:42,300
I need to go.

363
00:32:42,300 --> 00:32:44,280
Please stop acting nice!

364
00:32:44,280 --> 00:32:47,800
Stop telling me what to do or not to do, please!

365
00:33:03,240 --> 00:33:06,510
What are you doing? Get off.

366
00:33:06,510 --> 00:33:08,710
I won't get off until you do.

367
00:33:08,710 --> 00:33:11,470
Get off. There's no reason for you to be like this, too.

368
00:33:11,470 --> 00:33:14,280
Don't tell me what to do or not to do.

369
00:33:18,540 --> 00:33:20,410
Hwang Hee Tae, are you coming with us?

370
00:33:20,410 --> 00:33:21,840
Yes.

371
00:33:28,310 --> 00:33:31,860
[National Competition Sports Team]

372
00:33:38,240 --> 00:33:40,010
Dang, what's all this.

373
00:33:40,010 --> 00:33:42,190
Doctor! This way!

374
00:33:47,190 --> 00:33:50,040
Are you okay?

375
00:33:50,040 --> 00:33:52,680
Myeong Hee, I think it'll be faster if I move this patient.

376
00:33:54,100 --> 00:33:56,340
All right.

377
00:34:06,640 --> 00:34:08,840
Get in the ambulance! Hurry!

378
00:34:08,840 --> 00:34:11,330
Myeong Hee, hurry!

379
00:34:11,330 --> 00:34:14,050
Hurry.

380
00:34:33,950 --> 00:34:35,900
If you leave them twisted because that's how they were at the start,

381
00:34:35,900 --> 00:34:37,840
you're the one at a loss.

382
00:34:37,840 --> 00:34:40,370
Both your shoes and your training,

383
00:34:40,370 --> 00:34:43,560
isn't running well the most important thing?

384
00:35:02,340 --> 00:35:04,660
Where are you going? Get in the car. Let's go back.

385
00:35:04,660 --> 00:35:07,920
Hee Tae, that kid crying over there.

386
00:35:07,920 --> 00:35:10,860
Are you crazy? They're shooting.

387
00:35:11,490 --> 00:35:14,340
I need to go.

388
00:35:15,000 --> 00:35:16,380
Kim Myeong Hee!

389
00:35:16,380 --> 00:35:18,860
What if it's Myeong Soo?

390
00:35:20,440 --> 00:35:23,100
Why would Myeong Soo be here!

391
00:35:23,100 --> 00:35:25,040
Mister said he saw Myeong Soo

392
00:35:25,040 --> 00:35:28,260
struggling in the crowd.

393
00:35:28,260 --> 00:35:31,090
That's Myeong Soo's shoe.

394
00:35:37,400 --> 00:35:40,610
Myeong Hee! Myeong Hee!

395
00:35:46,780 --> 00:35:49,750
Who is that bitch?

396
00:35:49,750 --> 00:35:53,730
I'll go and catch them.

397
00:35:53,730 --> 00:35:55,230
Hey!

398
00:36:05,570 --> 00:36:07,490
Myeong Soo.

399
00:36:07,490 --> 00:36:09,260
Myeong Soo.

400
00:36:34,030 --> 00:36:36,030
If you don't want to shoot them, arrest them as fast as possible.

401
00:36:36,030 --> 00:36:38,440
Before someone else shoots.

402
00:36:56,060 --> 00:36:57,940
Kim Kyeong Soo.

403
00:37:06,830 --> 00:37:08,840
Hee Tae.

404
00:37:18,370 --> 00:37:20,080
Myeong Hee, what are you doing? Get in!

405
00:37:20,080 --> 00:37:21,990
Hwang Hee Tae!

406
00:37:28,120 --> 00:37:30,470
Myeong Hee, let's go.

407
00:37:30,470 --> 00:37:32,850
Hurry, Myeong Hee.

408
00:37:32,850 --> 00:37:35,560
Hurry along, Myeong Hee.

409
00:37:57,080 --> 00:38:00,680
Myeong Hee.

410
00:38:16,240 --> 00:38:19,580
How are you going to find them in this situation?

411
00:38:19,580 --> 00:38:23,330
If I'm late, make sure to feed the kids.

412
00:38:27,250 --> 00:38:29,070
You rascals!

413
00:38:29,070 --> 00:38:32,590
Coach, the People's Army!

414
00:38:32,590 --> 00:38:35,270
The People's Army is here!

415
00:38:35,270 --> 00:38:37,570
What?

416
00:38:50,050 --> 00:38:52,110
Here.

417
00:39:03,120 --> 00:39:06,860
Ma'am, did you get hurt?

418
00:39:06,860 --> 00:39:09,800
Your brother called earlier.

419
00:39:09,800 --> 00:39:12,730
He wanted you to know that he made it back to the dorm safely.

420
00:39:51,680 --> 00:39:54,970
Stop. What is it?

421
00:39:54,970 --> 00:39:57,740
Thank you for your service.

422
00:39:57,740 --> 00:40:00,250
I have some urgent business in Gwangju.

423
00:40:00,250 --> 00:40:03,950
Public transit is prohibited here. Please, go back.

424
00:40:03,950 --> 00:40:08,300
Please, Mister. I run a little business at the Yangdong Market.

425
00:40:08,300 --> 00:40:10,980
But my kids are in Gwangju.
[Identification card]

426
00:40:10,980 --> 00:40:13,950
Please let me through.

427
00:40:25,170 --> 00:40:27,570
Each person gets one.

428
00:40:27,570 --> 00:40:29,820
Priority to those who have already served their time in the military.

429
00:40:29,820 --> 00:40:32,100
Come forward!

430
00:40:40,170 --> 00:40:43,800
Hey. Where'd you get the guns?

431
00:40:43,800 --> 00:40:46,080
While roaming the reserve forces armory.

432
00:40:46,080 --> 00:40:48,460
What are you going to do, handing out the guns?

433
00:40:48,460 --> 00:40:51,080
Do you want to have some kind of war with the army?

434
00:40:51,080 --> 00:40:54,960
Then, should we just stand back and watch?

435
00:40:55,630 --> 00:40:58,250
Didn't you see today's flyers?

436
00:40:58,250 --> 00:41:02,730
That side is trying to frame us like rioters. If we give them a reason to—

437
00:41:02,730 --> 00:41:06,660
That side is starting a massacre. Why should we remain perfect and faultless?

438
00:41:06,660 --> 00:41:11,020
Is it lawful for them to shoot at civilians with no faults, but unlawful for us to fight against them?

439
00:41:11,020 --> 00:41:12,550
What is the law anyways?

440
00:41:12,550 --> 00:41:16,690
Wasn't the law created for the country to protect its people?

441
00:41:20,780 --> 00:41:25,490
You do what you need to. I'm going to do what I think is right.

442
00:41:26,210 --> 00:41:30,570
All right, priority to those who served in the military! Come out forward.

443
00:41:34,450 --> 00:41:36,570
Are you sure it's Lee Soo Chan?

444
00:41:38,540 --> 00:41:41,510
Don't worry about it. I'll go myself.

445
00:41:41,510 --> 00:41:44,630
All right. Keep me informed.

446
00:41:47,210 --> 00:41:49,050
What phone call was that?

447
00:41:49,050 --> 00:41:54,840
The rioters have seized armory.

448
00:41:54,840 --> 00:41:57,590
Things are proceeding well.

449
00:41:57,590 --> 00:41:59,220
[Hwang Ki Nam]

450
00:41:59,220 --> 00:42:01,620
What's with the long expression?

451
00:42:02,270 --> 00:42:04,860
Perhaps something to do with your son?

452
00:42:04,860 --> 00:42:08,130
Why are you bringing up my son all of a sudden?

453
00:42:08,130 --> 00:42:13,900
Your son's been arrested in Seoul before.

454
00:42:13,900 --> 00:42:16,140
While helping the Communists.

455
00:42:19,170 --> 00:42:24,370
If you're talking about the time he was arrested for performing emergency procedures on a suspect,

456
00:42:24,370 --> 00:42:28,120
it happened because my son was a medical student.

457
00:42:28,120 --> 00:42:30,980
He was found not guilty and released immediately.

458
00:42:32,270 --> 00:42:36,140
Just a coincidence, being at the wrong place at the wrong time?

459
00:42:36,140 --> 00:42:38,330
Then, that's a relief.

460
00:42:38,330 --> 00:42:40,750
But that crow...

461
00:42:44,850 --> 00:42:49,150
I mean your son. Where is he right now?

462
00:42:50,370 --> 00:42:54,190
He's living his newlywed life in Seoul.

463
00:42:55,410 --> 00:42:58,760
Seoul? Are you sure?

464
00:42:59,810 --> 00:43:05,490
You, Sir, are you here to monitor me?

465
00:43:11,530 --> 00:43:15,400
You never know, so make sure you take good care of your son.

466
00:43:15,400 --> 00:43:21,140
At such important times, being at the wrong place another time would raise suspicions.

467
00:43:58,500 --> 00:44:00,670
Bastard!

468
00:44:15,080 --> 00:44:17,020
Myeong Hee.

469
00:44:45,180 --> 00:44:48,120
Hee Tae, you were right.

470
00:44:49,910 --> 00:44:52,360
I'm a hypocrite.

471
00:44:56,380 --> 00:45:02,870
The moment I saw the face of the hurt child in the alley earlier,

472
00:45:05,020 --> 00:45:07,440
I was relieved.

473
00:45:08,140 --> 00:45:10,450
I was relieved that it wasn't Myeong Soo.

474
00:45:11,390 --> 00:45:16,610
That kid is also somebody's son, somebody's younger brother.

475
00:45:19,160 --> 00:45:22,670
But at that moment, I felt relieved.

476
00:45:29,670 --> 00:45:31,810
Is that so wrong?

477
00:45:35,270 --> 00:45:37,760
I'm relieved every second of the day, too.

478
00:45:37,760 --> 00:45:40,180
That it's not you.

479
00:45:42,260 --> 00:45:47,950
Are you a bad person for hoping your loved one to be safe?

480
00:45:49,120 --> 00:45:52,090
Then, I'll just be a bad person.

481
00:46:00,870 --> 00:46:04,620
The good people are always the ones that reflect on their actions.

482
00:46:04,620 --> 00:46:07,920
The bad ones see no fault.

483
00:46:11,090 --> 00:46:16,760
Real hypocrites don't even consider themselves hypocrites.

484
00:46:18,680 --> 00:46:24,480
I didn't say anything about Myeong Soo on purpose.

485
00:46:25,530 --> 00:46:28,310
Because I thought you wouldn't let me go.

486
00:46:28,310 --> 00:46:30,360
You did good.

487
00:46:31,430 --> 00:46:35,210
If I knew it was because of Myeong Soo, I would have never let you go.

488
00:46:35,210 --> 00:46:37,320
I would have gone by myself.

489
00:46:39,420 --> 00:46:43,060
I can't be in danger, but it's okay for you?

490
00:46:47,130 --> 00:46:50,190
Because there's nothing left for me.

491
00:46:52,160 --> 00:46:57,360
Even if something happens to me, you would still have Myeong Soo and

492
00:46:57,360 --> 00:46:59,740
your parents.

493
00:47:00,880 --> 00:47:04,230
But if I lose you, I have no one.

494
00:47:06,880 --> 00:47:11,610
So let me be the one to handle the dangerous things.

495
00:47:16,080 --> 00:47:20,690
I'm not telling you to do this or that, I'm asking you for this favor.

496
00:47:43,990 --> 00:47:45,920
Don't worry.

497
00:47:45,920 --> 00:47:48,610
It's because it's cold.

498
00:47:56,030 --> 00:47:57,690
What happened?

499
00:47:57,690 --> 00:48:01,060
Did the People's Army really come?

500
00:48:01,060 --> 00:48:03,510
They're not the People's Army.

501
00:48:04,450 --> 00:48:07,040
They were our country's military.

502
00:48:07,040 --> 00:48:12,720
I'm telling you they were the People's Army. Why would our military shoot our people?

503
00:48:12,720 --> 00:48:16,620
Why did the military turn into villains suddenly?

504
00:48:16,620 --> 00:48:20,790
Hey, even in Mazinga Z. The real villain is

505
00:48:20,790 --> 00:48:23,660
Dr. Hell who is trying to take over the world.

506
00:48:23,660 --> 00:48:28,560
Wouldn't the military men also have someone behind them who's the real villain?

507
00:48:36,900 --> 00:48:39,020
Catch that bastard.

508
00:48:39,020 --> 00:48:41,130
Hurry.

509
00:48:42,590 --> 00:48:43,600
Follow me!

510
00:48:43,600 --> 00:48:45,570
Follow me!

511
00:48:48,190 --> 00:48:49,270
Follow me!

512
00:48:49,270 --> 00:48:51,130
Come here!

513
00:48:53,880 --> 00:48:56,230
Take that bastard.

514
00:49:07,490 --> 00:49:11,730
Then, who's the real villain?

515
00:49:11,730 --> 00:49:15,270
What are they trying to overtake?

516
00:49:15,270 --> 00:49:18,590
I can't stand this childish conversation!

517
00:49:39,960 --> 00:49:42,510
Mr. Hwang...

518
00:49:47,260 --> 00:49:50,380
You ended up in a situation in which you need my help.

519
00:49:50,380 --> 00:49:53,580
I can't help you twice, so be careful.

520
00:49:54,320 --> 00:49:59,130
By any chance, do you know where your sister is?

521
00:49:59,130 --> 00:50:01,270
I can't contact her.

522
00:50:09,230 --> 00:50:15,680
The car is waiting outside. Don't go out in the meantime and just rest.

523
00:50:15,680 --> 00:50:18,250
Sir...

524
00:50:18,250 --> 00:50:21,220
Please let the others go, too.

525
00:50:21,220 --> 00:50:25,350
Please, they are all people who've been dragged here with no sins.

526
00:50:25,350 --> 00:50:27,010
Those that are hurt.

527
00:50:27,010 --> 00:50:29,800
Or at least the young ones.

528
00:50:36,130 --> 00:50:39,780
Stop with the gibberish and live quietly.

529
00:50:39,780 --> 00:50:44,450
I really want to throw your entire family in there but I'm holding back.
(Gwangju dialect)

530
00:51:02,460 --> 00:51:05,080
Stick 'em right into the ground!

531
00:51:05,820 --> 00:51:11,990
Mr. Private First Class Kim Kyung Soo still isn't ready to use his gun.

532
00:51:15,200 --> 00:51:18,300
Open your eyes. Look at me properly.

533
00:51:18,300 --> 00:51:21,460
You have to see the mess everyone's in, all because of you.

534
00:51:22,180 --> 00:51:26,540
How about now? Are you ready to use your gun now?

535
00:51:32,180 --> 00:51:33,520
Oh, right.

536
00:51:33,520 --> 00:51:35,960
Whether your comrades die or not,

537
00:51:35,960 --> 00:51:39,700
you still care more about the rebels.

538
00:51:49,460 --> 00:51:51,370
Damn it.

539
00:51:52,130 --> 00:51:56,950
Kim Kyung Soo, you're not a virtuous person.

540
00:51:58,040 --> 00:52:01,340
There is no such thing as a virtuous person.

541
00:52:01,340 --> 00:52:04,840
It's about always making the best possible decisions.

542
00:52:06,250 --> 00:52:12,180
And the thing is, you don't hand over the burden of making those decisions to someone else.

543
00:52:12,180 --> 00:52:16,820
That isn't being virtuous. That's being strong.

544
00:52:17,650 --> 00:52:20,550
I like you because you're strong.

545
00:52:24,030 --> 00:52:26,500
She was a nurse.

546
00:52:32,430 --> 00:52:33,670
What?

547
00:52:33,670 --> 00:52:37,150
I cannot shoot someone who isn't a rebel.

548
00:53:01,780 --> 00:53:03,230
Myeong Hee! What are you doing? Hurry and get in!

549
00:53:03,230 --> 00:53:05,320
Hwang Hee Tae!

550
00:53:07,230 --> 00:53:09,140
Hey, stop the car!

551
00:53:16,560 --> 00:53:18,840
Seok Cheol is alive.

552
00:53:21,310 --> 00:53:23,580
She's in Gwangju right now.

553
00:54:04,170 --> 00:54:05,840
You don't have to give us a ride.

554
00:54:05,840 --> 00:54:09,250
I'm just dropping you off on my way to picking up blood supplies.

555
00:54:09,250 --> 00:54:13,010
We're comrades who fought together through life and death. Of course, I can do this much.

556
00:54:13,010 --> 00:54:15,390
You just need to be dropped off at the train station?

557
00:54:16,890 --> 00:54:20,150
Let's go see Myeong Soo before going to the station.

558
00:54:21,630 --> 00:54:23,990
Can we?

559
00:54:23,990 --> 00:54:26,760
You'll only be relieved after you see him.

560
00:54:26,760 --> 00:54:29,280
And we can return Myeong Soo's shoe.

561
00:54:30,350 --> 00:54:33,190
Ah, my blood sugar's shooting up.

562
00:54:33,190 --> 00:54:36,350
Then where is it. Where should I drop you off?

563
00:54:36,350 --> 00:54:37,760
Before the terminal—

564
00:54:37,760 --> 00:54:39,810
Myeong Hee!

565
00:54:49,350 --> 00:54:52,350
Why are you here?

566
00:54:52,350 --> 00:54:56,040
Follow me, quickly. Myeong Soo is waiting, too.

567
00:54:56,040 --> 00:54:57,880
We were on our way to the dorms, too.

568
00:54:57,880 --> 00:54:59,980
Let's go to Naju.

569
00:54:59,980 --> 00:55:02,320
This is not the place to be anymore.

570
00:55:02,320 --> 00:55:05,170
Take Myeong Soo. I'll take care of myself.

571
00:55:05,170 --> 00:55:07,090
Kim Myeong Hee!

572
00:55:16,370 --> 00:55:18,740
Then I shall go and help Dr. Yoo with something...

573
00:55:18,740 --> 00:55:20,360
No, you don't have to do that.

574
00:55:20,360 --> 00:55:23,460
I was in need of an extra pair of hands!

575
00:55:23,460 --> 00:55:26,140
I'll get the car going.

576
00:55:27,660 --> 00:55:30,570
Why don't you two talk in private?

577
00:56:05,660 --> 00:56:08,990
Why's a relationship between a father and a daughter that cold?

578
00:56:08,990 --> 00:56:12,500
Looks like you'll suffer quite a bit once you get married.

579
00:56:12,500 --> 00:56:16,900
I wondered where Myeong Hee got her stone-cold attitude. Now I know she got it from her father.

580
00:56:16,900 --> 00:56:21,910
What do you mean, stone-cold. She's too much of a softie, that it makes me upset.

581
00:56:21,910 --> 00:56:23,840
You're already blinded by love, I see.

582
00:56:23,840 --> 00:56:26,180
Nothing can beat that, nothing.

583
00:56:29,130 --> 00:56:32,680
But how did the station receive enough blood supply to share?

584
00:56:32,680 --> 00:56:34,360
Blood donations.

585
00:56:34,360 --> 00:56:36,860
There were that many employees' blood donations?

586
00:56:36,860 --> 00:56:38,730
No, regular citizens.

587
00:56:38,730 --> 00:56:44,160
I made some announcements that we were short on blood, and there were a ton of people who volunteered to donate.

588
00:56:56,690 --> 00:56:59,270
Why? Is it a song you like?

589
00:56:59,270 --> 00:57:03,330
Not me, but my friend.

590
00:57:08,260 --> 00:57:10,350
What is this?

591
00:57:28,350 --> 00:57:31,860
[Gwangju Peace Hospital]

592
00:57:31,860 --> 00:57:35,610
How many times do I have to tell you I'm not going!

593
00:57:36,500 --> 00:57:40,290
Why? Did that guy ask you to be with him?

594
00:57:40,290 --> 00:57:42,040
Does he want to get married?

595
00:57:42,040 --> 00:57:45,120
Don't worry about how I live my life.

596
00:57:45,120 --> 00:57:47,450
What about his parents?

597
00:57:47,450 --> 00:57:49,520
Do they know you're seeing each other?

598
00:57:49,520 --> 00:57:53,430
How can you trust someone that won't even introduce you to them?!

599
00:57:54,410 --> 00:57:57,270
Don't regret this later. Let's go to Naju.

600
00:57:57,270 --> 00:58:01,290
You don't know a thing, don't say that...

601
00:58:01,290 --> 00:58:03,260
Ma'am!

602
00:58:04,960 --> 00:58:08,620
Dr. Byeong Cheol and Hee Tae...

603
00:58:17,360 --> 00:58:23,360
♫ You, who are too beautiful it hurts ♫

604
00:58:24,920 --> 00:58:31,000
♫ You, who would smile with sad eyes ♫

605
00:58:32,320 --> 00:58:34,190
♫ You, who came to me like destiny and gave your love to me ♫

606
00:58:34,190 --> 00:58:35,850
What are you talking about? They went out together!

607
00:58:35,850 --> 00:58:37,460
There was only one person at the scene!

608
00:58:37,460 --> 00:58:40,090
I don't even know if he's dying somewhere.

609
00:58:40,090 --> 00:58:41,690
But there's nothing I can do.

610
00:58:41,690 --> 00:58:44,030
I heard they found Hwang Hee Tae and are holding onto him.

611
00:58:44,030 --> 00:58:45,340
Did they really say that?

612
00:58:45,340 --> 00:58:47,330
He'll end up ruining your life, too!

613
00:58:47,330 --> 00:58:49,880
He's not the one that ruined my life. It's you!

614
00:58:49,880 --> 00:58:53,750
I'm going to kill your entire family.

615
00:58:53,750 --> 00:58:56,530
Brother Hee Tae might die.

616
00:58:56,530 --> 00:58:57,700
What do you mean?

617
00:58:57,700 --> 00:59:00,280
Even if the lightning strikes here, I won't budge.

618
00:59:00,280 --> 00:59:03,023
So that you can find me.
